Thank you. Your last question will come from Tim Horan of Oppenheimer. Sir, your line is open.

Timothy Horan -- Oppenheimer & Co. Inc. -- Analyst

Thanks guys. Can you give us some color around how many fixed wireless subs you think you can have kind of longer term and what -- when do we kind of ramp up to kind of full ability to add kind of customers on a monthly basis. What do you think that run rate would look like?

Hans Vestberg -- Chairman and Chief Executive Officer

Thank you. On the fixed wireless access customers, as I said, we have now two offerings in the market. We have one, which is 4G and then of course we have the 5G which is a big push for us. We have said we're going to address 30 million households over the five to eight years, that's where we -- what we're addressing and hopefully, not hopefully, our ambition is to take a fair market share of that one as we've done with the Fios.

So that's what we're pushing for and our team is always geared to do better than the expectations. So of course we are pushing them hard and as we are releasing more and more sites and more and more homes for sale. We're going to start reporting it.

Timothy Horan -- Oppenheimer & Co. Inc. -- Analyst

And how important is the new equipment? How much better is it and how easy is it to install?

Hans Vestberg -- Chairman and Chief Executive Officer

It is a step change. I would say it's clearly a step change when it comes to both the self-install, but also how much more we can cover with that CPE, because it's bringing so much more of the signal compared -- remember, the first CPE we had was basically smartphone chipset sitting in the CPE, that's what we had.

So basically, we had a smartphone being the CPE. This is catered for being an indoor or outdoor CPE and we have reported before, we have a lot of indoor installations right now because this is working very well. So it is a step change. And mainly because we can address so many more households from one radio base station. That's the importance of it.

Timothy Horan -- Oppenheimer & Co. Inc. -- Analyst

Thank you.

